column5: Just want ya,ll to know myself and memart are safely at the camp,but I for one can  honestly say,I feel the pain for you dial up users. The drive up this morning was cold,creeks and shallow lakes had a crust of ice on them.The forecast is not good,rain and warmer temps for the week. Excitement for the mornings drive was I almost got smoked by a flyby grouse on the way up. Cold ones are pretty much gone    it,s  getting close to sandman time. Up at 4 am,will post the days results later monday.  Oh and if my wife is reading this, goodnight deer
Enjoy...and I am one of those who now suffer with dial-up, and I agree, it does suck
up at 4 am.........can't hunt in the dark....830/9:00  is a better time  oh well good luck
'cougars' hunt in the dark.....be afraid Brian, be very very afraid
The Grouse should'a nailed ya!!! ... it's only fair for the critters to get a lick in every once in a while!!!  Have fun and be careful Bubba!!!
